== R
My quick introduciton to R is [https://youtu.be/Kh0AVf8LPNw here].\n

To get RStudio on you computer, you need to first download and install [https://mirror.las.iastate.edu/CRAN/ R] then you need to download and install [https://rstudio.com/products/rstudio/download/ RStudio].

Further,  I recommend doing those two courses on DataCamp. 
- [https://www.datacamp.com/courses/free-introduction-to-r Introduction to R]
- [https://www.datacamp.com/courses/introduction-to-data Introduction to Data]\n\n

{{<p>}}
In addition, Booth offers access to an online R tutorial on LinkedinLearning. To access the training, go to: [https://linkedinlearning.uchicago.edu here] and login using your CNetID and password. You may find it helpful to work through the following R courses offered on LinkedInLearning:
{{</p>}}
- Code Clinic: R with Mark Niemann-Ross

- R Statistics Essential Training with Barton Poulson

- Up and Running with R with Barton Poulson

